<title>ITALY: Italy's Bologna sees August CPI up 3.5 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Bologna sees August CPI up 3.5 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>BOLOGNA, Italy 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Bologna said its August consumer price index stood at 0.0 percent month-on-month and 3.5 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In July, Bologna's inflation rate fell 0.1 percent and grew 3.6 percent year on year.</p>
<p>Bologna is one of 10 Italian cities publishing inflation yesterday and today.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 7.62 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to July 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.0   (-0.1)    3.5  (3.6)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.4   (-0.3)    3.7  (4.1)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0    (0.2)    2.9  (2.9)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.3   (-1.1)    5.8  (5.5)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.1    (0.0)    3.1  (3.1)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.1   (-0.4)    4.6  (4.3)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.3    (0.3)    4.6  (4.5)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.0    (0.0)    3.9  (4.1)</p>
<p>    Education			  -0.3    (0.0)    2.7  (3.0)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.0    (0.0)    2.8  (2.8)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.1   (-0.3)    1.6  (1.5)</p>
